President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Bruce J. Sherrick for the position of Member of the Board of Directors of the Federal Agricultural Mortgage Corporation. Dr. Sherrick is currently a Professor of Agricultural and Applied Finance and the Director of the Center for Farm and Rural Business Finance at the University of Illinois. His research focuses on risk analysis, crop insurance evaluation, and modeling of financial institutions. Dr. Sherrick is also a managing partner at integrated Financial Analytics & Research (iFAR), a consulting firm specializing in credit risk assessment and modeling of agricultural finance institutions. He is also involved in the development of decision tools for agricultural producers and lenders, and contributes to the farmdoc website. Dr. Sherrick holds a Ph.D. in Finance and Marketing from The Ohio State University.